<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="7" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1158,1761]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,324,1194,1220]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
This species differs from the other species of the family occurring in the freshwaters of the country by the following combination of characters: teeth pointed, conical, without second cusp on premaxillary and mandibular teeth of the 1st series; lips thick and large, the lower lip continuous, without a frenum (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Bussing, W. A." pageId="6" pageNumber="7" refId="ref63850" refString="Bussing, W. A. (1998). Freshwater fishes of Costa Rica. Editorial Universidad de Costa Rica, San Jose, Costa Rica, 468 pp." type="book" year="1998">Bussing 1998</bibRefCitation>
); cheek scale series 4–5 (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Rican, O. &amp; Pialek, L. &amp; Dragova, K. &amp; Novak, J." box="[535,729,1302,1331]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" pagination="1 - 102" refId="ref66138" refString="Rican, O., Pialek, L., Dragova, K. &amp; Novak, J. (2016) Diversity and evolution of the Middle American cichlid fishes (Teleostei: Cichlidae) with revised classification. Vertebrate Zoology, 66 (1), 1 - 102." type="journal article" year="2016">
Říčan 
<emphasis box="[606,662,1302,1328]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">et al.</emphasis>
2016
</bibRefCitation>
); dorsal fin spines 16–17; and anal fin spines 6–7. Furthermore, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Gunther" baseAuthorityYear="1864" box="[151,272,1338,1365]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cichlidae" genus="Amphilophus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="labiatus">
<emphasis box="[151,272,1338,1365]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">A. labiatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from the closely related 
<taxonomicName authority="(Gunther, 1864)" baseAuthorityName="Gunther" baseAuthorityYear="1864" box="[626,1079,1338,1365]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cichlidae" genus="Amphilophus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="citrinellus">
<emphasis box="[626,894,1338,1364]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Amphilophus citrinellus</emphasis>
(Günther, 1864)
</taxonomicName>
by having a larger (37.8–39.5% of Standard Length – SL; vs. 35.0–35.6% of SL) and thinner (Head Depth – HD = 79.9–90.9% of Head Length – HL; vs. HD = 111.5–118.9 of HL) head and a larger (42.8–43.4% of HL; vs. 40.4–41.9% of HL) snout. See 
<bibRefCitation author="Stauffer Jr., J. R. &amp; McKaye, K. R." pageId="6" pageNumber="7" pagination="1 - 18" refId="ref66696" refString="Stauffer Jr., J. R. &amp; McKaye, K. R. (2002) Descriptions of three new species of cichlid fishes (Teleostei: Cichlidae) from Lake Xiloa, Nicaragua. Cuadernos de Investigacion de la Universidad de Centro America, 12, 1 - 18." type="journal article" year="2002">Stauffer &amp; McKaye (2002)</bibRefCitation>
for a detailed comparative analysis.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="7" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1158,1761]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
